<Resp>None< /Resp>< review>
This Donut Shop has truly earned it’s Title. For they’ll only have Donuts and Croissants at the ready during Sunrise. They’re Opened at 5am everyday and if you wish to have breakfast, I’m afraid you’ll have to be there before 8am. Why? Because by 8am they’ll surely not have what you want, whether it’s a Specific type of Donut  you like or that delicious Ham & Cheese Croissant. By this time (8am) you’ll only be limited to whatever’s left on Display and they will not Make any more Batches for you upon Request. I taken it’s because they just simply don’t wanna risk having too many Leftovers at de end of their Hours of Operation. Which I actually don’t know when they Close. However.... Despite their Negligence of Customer Satisfaction, Unknown Closing time, and Limited Information posted on Google Maps; when you’re here early enough to actually have what you want it is very Delicious. Just ensure you’re here before 8am.<//review>

<text>My experience was excellent.  The staff was friendly and informative from scheduling my appointment to the actual exam. Given the current pandemic, all protocols were practice to ensure the safety of patients and employees.

They maximized technology through text message and online links for scheduling and prescreening questions. On the day of my appointment, verbal questions through phone and notification when they were ready for to enter was on point. Once I entered the office, there was hand sanitizer, signage, and floor markings to help with social distancing.

The cool thing was the use of technology for the dilation process (no drops thank goodness). The good part is the shortened dilation and sensitivity to light. The bad part is insurance companies (at least my insurance) do not cover the cost ($30). But, it was worth the out of pocket fee for convenience and safety of the staff.

The staff and doctor were friendly and explained everything to me with hesitation. That is why they are my go to for my annual exams. And at 43, I do not have to wear glasses (knock on wood). Thanks Dr. Gaylord and team for the service.<//text>< Pics>

<review>Coinbase will fool you with ease of use; however, it will cost you your assets.  I placed some of my crypto in their vault, which is more secure.  I attempted to withdraw it to my wallet so that I could send it to my Ledger; when a withdrawal is initiated Coinbase sends two approval emails with links.  One goes to your primary email and the other to your secondary email.  When I received the emails I clicked on the link to approve the withdrawal in my primary email and it worked fine; however, when I clicked on the link in my secondary email it sent me to the Coinbase site and stated that this function was already completed, yet it continued to reflect unapproved.  I cancelled the withdrawal and attempted it again and again and again, you get the point.  The link does not execute the intended function on the Coinbase website.  I contacted customer service through the form and I get completely useless information with no indication that they intend to correct the problem; furthermore, once they give you the generic answer, you don't hear from them again.  Their generic answer was to cancel the withdrawal and initiate another withdrawal to generate new emails.  This is not the issue and it is clear that I've already done that. <review>Coinbase has the worst customer service I have ever had.  Ever.  They offer no productive response--you just get stuck in a loop.  Sure, you can get someone on the phone, but they will tell you that they can only answer questions, and that if you have a problem, they'll just forward your issues to the specialists that actually handle your account.  Mind you, your account may or may not contain THOUSANDS of dollars you deposited.

Then they'll tell you that the specialist who will actually resolve your issue is really, very backed up---quite horribly behind on a list of millions of other problems people are having with Coinbase, but they'll reassure you that, EVENTUALLY, via email, they WILL reach out to you... just wait, they WILL email you.

However, when you eventually get the email, Coinbase's response will be a generic email, not signed by anyone or with any contact information.  You'll only get a link back to their support site, or through some link to read about all of the digital ways that can handle issues that aren't your specific problem.  So you'll spend weeks trying the instructions in the email, getting no results, then calling phone support, which will generate another email, which you'll follow the instructions, which won't work, so you'll call phone support, and they'll generate another email...

You'll just get a generic email with no name or title about the person handling your horrible, horrible experience with Coinbase... nor will you get any contact information about who to talk to about handling your account... you know, the one with your MONEY in it.

I've been locked out of my account and away from my MONEY for TWO MONTHS and have had to speak to someone DIFFERENT and EQUALLY IGNORANT of my situation EVERY TIME.  I have had to explain why I am calling EVERY TIME!!! I STILL no access to my account.  I still have no resolution!  I am still told to just wait for another email!!! I hope everyone at Coinbase finds a successful future with many, many happy memories.

<username>RAY B<//username><Review>2nd update; Found a solution without help from coinbase. If you have the same issue I experienced, this may work for you as well.  I had a RESTRICTED ACCOUNT.
Download the mobile app for coinbase (to your mobile device obviously)
link your bank account (make sure the name is exactly the same on coinbase, and your bank account, otherwise you will freeze that app as well)
transfer a small amount to your coinbase account.
this should reset your account,  it should be fully functioning instantly on your PC.

< text>
I thank my lucky stars for finding Los Alamitos Dental Care - my favorite place to go for ALL of my dental care. Dr. Kerry Hahn is a true professional with a passion for dentistry. He explains in detail exactly what to expect from any if his procedures, no surprises. He makes sure that you do not experience pain or discomfort. His work is good and consistent, always works with the best of intention and with a positive disposition. The office itself is a nice place to be, filled with a wonderful support staff and Dentists. It's always cheerful, clean, safe and everyone is always ready to help. Almost every office has a window with a nice view, soothing music plays in the background and everything is clean and ready for each patient. The office uses state of the art technology and is a one stop shop for everything you need in a Dentist office. I trust them completely with my oral care and I always look forward to my appointments there. If you are looking for a great, dependable and professional dental office, I highly recommend Los Alamitos Dental Care for you.< /text>

They made the estimate the next day and text me  about the damage and after my approval they began to repair it. My technician Robert kept me inform about the progress through email every morning and they repair it very fast. I got my car back in 10 days and I am very satisfied with the result. I highly recommend this company and specialty this branch in OC, Ca.</Text>

<UserId.>116672109955993068517< /UserId.>< Text>
Best car experience! Staff was a uper helpful, friendly and trustworthy!!
Here's the long story: I took my Fiat into Kings Service on Fair oaks because both of my headlights were out. It isn't exactly what they normally do, but they said they'd look. I waited less then 5 min. Turned out the fuses were fine, just needed new bulbs, which they didn't have on hand but told me if I wanted to get them they would install. There was a nearby place that sold the bulbs, which I bought and brought back.
Without needing to wait at all they not only installed the bulbs for FREE but showed me exactly how to do it, so that next time I can do it it myself! I left so happy! I will definitely go back the next time I need a repair!</Text>

<UserId.>115014572107201681557</UserId.>< Review>
So nice to not have to take my king sized blankets to a local laundromat! LWL arrived 2 days after I initially signed up for their services within the time frame that I signed up for. I also saw that they pickup/drop off late at night, as an option, which I thought could be convenient- if needed. I took a star off because I was not informed (nor was there information on their website) about their COVID-19 requirement that all laundry must be sealed/covered by a bag. I didn’t have any type of bag large enough to fit 2 king-sized comforters - so I put them in my laundry basket for the pickup-person. She was nearly about to leave without taking my laundry until she figured she’d go to car to give me one of their laundry bags (which they give you, complimentary, when they return your laundry the first time). It all worked out, but could’ve been more convenient (the pickup person could’ve just picked it up from my doorstep) had I know to seal everything in a bag. Also, the cost doubled from the time I made an initial payment online to the time they weighed my laundry - so roughly a bit over $80 in total....not their fault, but still was a lot more than I expected. Either way, I will be using them again!<//Review>

The process for signing up for a loan is very easy to do and very fast. I was able to get money in my account within 24. The staff is very friendly and easy to work with. Only complaints are that they ask for a work number and say they will not call it but they do. They also call nonstop after applying. But my main issue was the insanely high interest rate!! If you are desperate then that may work for you but I will never apply for a loan again through here with interest rates like that.
